## Build & Deployment Architecture

### Vite Projects (Standard)

**Development:**
- Dev server starts in 1-3 seconds (vs 15-30s with CRA)
- Hot Module Replacement (HMR) updates in <100ms
- Runs on port 5173 by default

**Production Build:**
1. `pnpm run build` → Compiles to `dist/`
2. Optimized, minified, tree-shaken bundles
3. Assets include hash for cache busting

**Docker Deployment:**
1. Multi-stage build (node:20-alpine → nginx:alpine)
2. Build stage: Install deps → Build → ~3-5 minutes
3. Runtime stage: Nginx serves static files → ~20MB image
4. Health checks every 30s
5. Access via gateway at http://localhost:8080/<app-name>/

### WAR Deployment to Tomcat

**Projects with WAR deployment:**
- fees-comparison-dashboard
- aucdt-analytics-dashboard
- kanban-app
- applicant-dashboard
- lecturer-assessment-system

**Build Process (Bitbucket Pipelines):**
```bash
1. cd $PROJECT_DIR
2. corepack enable && corepack prepare pnpm@latest --activate
3. pnpm install --frozen-lockfile
4. pnpm run build                    # → dist/
5. mkdir -p dist/WEB-INF
6. cp -varf ./WEB-INF/* dist/WEB-INF/
7. cd dist && zip -r app.war *
8. scp app.war root@66.226.72.199:/opt/tomcat/webapps/
```

**WEB-INF Structure:**
```
project/
├── WEB-INF/
│   └── web.xml              # Servlet configuration for Tomcat
├── dist/                    # Build output (created during build)
├── src/
└── package.json
```

**Deployment Target:**
- Server: 66.226.72.199
- Container: Tomcat 9
- Path: /opt/tomcat/webapps/
- Access: https://[domain]/[app-name]/

### Backend API Deployment

**Development:**
```bash
cd backend
npm run dev                  # ts-node-dev with hot reload
# Access: http://localhost:3000
```

**Production:**
```bash
npm run build                # TypeScript → dist/
npm start                    # node dist/server.js
```

**Docker:**
```bash
# Via docker-compose-all-apps.yml (includes backend)
docker-compose -f docker-compose-all-apps.yml up tuc-auth-api

# Standalone
cd backend
docker build -t tuc-auth-api .
docker run -p 3000:3000 --env-file .env tuc-auth-api
```

**API Endpoints (typical):**
```
POST /api/auth/register      # User registration
POST /api/auth/login         # User login
GET  /api/auth/verify        # JWT verification
POST /api/auth/refresh       # Refresh token
GET  /health                 # Health check endpoint
```

## Key Architectural Patterns

### Frontend: Custom Hooks Pattern

```javascript
// hooks/useAnalyticsData.js
import { useState, useEffect, useMemo } from 'react';

export const useAnalyticsData = (filters) => {
  const [data, setData] = useState(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
  const [error, setError] = useState(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    // Fetch and validate data
  }, [filters]);

  const processedMetrics = useMemo(() => {
    // Expensive calculations memoized
    return calculateMetrics(data);
  }, [data]);

  return { data, loading, error, processedMetrics };
};
```

### Frontend: State Management

```javascript
// Loading, Error, Empty states pattern
{loading && <LoadingState />}
{error && <ErrorState error={error} onRetry={retry} />}
{!loading && !error && !data?.length && <EmptyState />}
{data && <MainContent data={data} />}
```

### Frontend: Utility-Based Calculations

```javascript
// utils/analyticsCalculations.js
export const processRawData = (data) => { /* pure function */ };
export const calculateYearlyData = (data) => { /* pure function */ };
export const calculateTrends = (data) => { /* pure function */ };
```

### Backend: MVC with Services

```
routes/authRoutes.ts         → Define endpoints
controllers/authController.ts → Handle requests
services/authService.ts      → Business logic
models/User.ts               → Data models
middleware/auth.ts           → JWT verification
```

### Testing: Page Object Model (Playwright)

```typescript
// utils/BasePage.ts
export class BasePage {
  constructor(protected page: Page) {}

  async navigateTo(url: string) {
    await this.page.goto(url);
  }
}

// utils/LoginPage.ts
export class LoginPage extends BasePage {
  private emailInput = '#email';

  async login(email: string, password: string) {
    await this.page.fill(this.emailInput, email);
    await this.page.fill('#password', password);
    await this.page.click('button[type="submit"]');
  }
}
```

